This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the chairmen and ranking members of various committees in the House and Senate. In the letter, the President informs them of his designations of five foreign individuals as appropriate for sanctions under the Foreign Narcotics Kingpin Designation Act. The individuals designated are Haji Agha Jan Alizai from Afghanistan, Haji Bando from Afghanistan, Ousmane Conte from Guinea, Sergio Enrique Villarreal Barragan from Mexico, and Mohamed Bachir Suleman from Mozambique. The President states that he has directed sanctions against these individuals under the Kingpin Act. The letter is dated June 1, 2010, and is addressed to the relevant committee members.